SIMPLE: chayote
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chayote
<hw>Cha"yo"te</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>a tropical West Indian
vine (<spn>Sechium edule</spn>) of the gourd family, which bears small
white flowers and produces an edible fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the edible fruit of the <er>chayote{1}</er> vine,
having a pear shape with a furrowed skin, and usually green or white. It
is also called <altname>choyote</altname>,
<altname>christophene</altname>, <altname>mirliton</altname>, and
<altname>vegetable pear</altname></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chazy epoch</ent>⟦br⟧
